{"questionId":"2738028","questionHtml":"<p>By using a suitable transformation from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi></math>, or otherwise, find the roots of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><msup><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><msup><mi>w</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>compares <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><msup><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><msup><mi>w</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>w</mi></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>z</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mtext>i</mtext></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to fac